title: Nazareth girls tennis team wins first District 11 title in program history
text:
Complete Box Score » 
Nazareth 3, Southern Lehigh 2 — Rapid Recap 
Nazareth girls tennis team defeated Southern Lehigh 3-2 on Saturday at Northwood Racquet Club in Palmer Township to win its first District 11 Class AAA title in program history. 
Turning point : Sophomore Emma Haynes and freshman Jenn Soika rallied from a set down to earn a 3-6, 6-4, 6-1 victory over Southern Lehigh's Keelin McLoughlin and Kelly Asselin at No. 2 doubles and clinch the championship. Also, Southern Lehigh forfeited the No. 1 singles match as two-time district champion Nina DeLuna is in a USTA junior national championship event in South Carolina. 
Top performers: Haynes and Soika didn't show their nerves as the sophomore and freshman rallied for the match-clinching victory. Freshman Halle DeNardo and junior Madison Stewart had a 6-2, 6-1 win at No 1 doubles to keep their perfect record intact for the season. 
What it means : The Blue Eagles make school history with their first girls or boys district tennis team title. Nazareth will play against District 1 runner-up Conestoga in the first round of the state tournament at 2 p.m. Tuesday at Winning Touch Tennis in Allentown.
